error.signature: TS2394: This overload signature is not compatible with its implementation signature

verdict.summary: The implementation signature must be compatible with all overload signatures. It must accept a superset of all parameter types.

dead_ends.action: Make each overload signature identical to the implementation
dead_ends.why_fails: Defeats the purpose of overloads; overloads should provide narrower type signatures for callers

workarounds.action: Ensure the implementation signature accepts all overload parameter types
Use a union type in the implementation for return types

leads_to.condition: When fixing overload signatures changes caller compatibility

preceded_by.condition: When adding new overloads to fix call-site errors

frequently_confused_with.distinction: TS2769 is at the call site (caller doesn't match any overload); TS2394 is at the definition (overload doesn't match implementation)
